TO prove my dedication to this 30 day yoga journey, I couldn't find time in my morning or afternoon or early evening for day 4, but I was determined to do it and stay on schedule.

So, at 11pm, when I would have gone to bed (after the tennis), I switched on youtube and found Day 4 and for the next half hour, I spent time on the mat going through the motions of this session.

It was the best thing I had done for myself all day, after an extremely hot afternoon and then a good portion of the night, being spent babysitting my nieces.  I had wanted to do something for myself all day and I was so surprised that I was itching to do yoga in my day and I think if it was anything else, I wouldn't have cared if I had missed the day.

I keep on saying how great I feel afterwards, and I have even taken it upon myself to spend extra time afterwards laying on the mat with my eyes closed and relaxed and tuned into mediation music.  I feel as though this yoga journey has put me on a really good path as I am always trying to find ways of relaxing and sometimes sitting doesn't do it for me, but these movements and concentration on every breath always puts me in a good place.

I am really looking forward to continuing this journey and seeing what can challenge me and what can put me at peace through my day.

My favourite thing about home yoga is that I've stopped thinking about what I look like and just focus on how it feels (in fact most days I have my eyes closed for half the practice). I used to feel so embarrassed taking a wide seat because I'm so inflexible there - I would try and do it the way other people were and got nothing out of it. Now I sit on a block (not even a blankie!) and my legs are barely a metre apart, but I can feel the stretch! And while I'm not seeing improvement on the may yet, I notice it everyday when I'm off - in my posture and a sort of inner strength I never felt before.

I've realized that the beginning position (sitting cross-legged) is NOT a comfortable posture for me! I struggle a lot to keep my legs crossed and my back straight and I'm trembling the entire time. It's more comfortable for me to grip my ankles. Anyway, I still stuck with it and completed today's practice. Yay me!

Good morning from Scotland Adriene (and Benji)!Thank you for another amazing practice. I found today physically easier, although I had to go easy on some of the poses, but what was most interesting today was all the emotions that came up for me during the practice. On a rational level I know there is no shame in not being able to do the wide-leg forward fold very well, but in this pose, and as I chose to stay in the twist in the other pose, I could hear a horrible dialogue in my mind, telling me that I am weak, or a failure. I think the emotions that came up for me in this practice highlight a broader issue that I experience off the mat. I have to learn to be kind to myself, and to be aware that looking after myself, and not to be always pushing and pushing, is something to be strived for, not punish myself for. Thank you so much for giving me the opportunity to have these experiences. x
